A constructor is a special method that is called when an instance of a class is created. It initializes the new object

What are the types of constructors?

Default Constructor: A constructor with no parameters.
Parameterized Constructor: A constructor with parameters.
Copy Constructor (Not a standard Java feature but can be implemented).


Can a constructor be private?

Yes, a constructor can be private. This is often used in the Singleton design pattern

The this keyword is used to refer to the current instance of the class. It is often used to resolve naming 
conflicts between instance variables and parameters.
Yes, you can call one constructor from another in the same class using this()